articles.description: Shouldn't the Spartans take over the top spot after they beat Purdue and after Villanova and Virginia lost? Not so fast. Michigan State's body of work doesn't compare to its elite competition.
articles.headline: College hoops Power Rankings: Why Michigan State is not ready to be No. 1

images.caption: Miles Bridges and Michigan State enjoyed knocking off  Purdue on Saturday.
images.name: Purdue vs. Michigan State (Miles Bridges) [608x342]

images.caption: No. 4 Michigan State overcomes a double-digit deficit in the first half and gets a go-ahead 3-pointer from Miles Bridges in the final seconds to beat No. 3 Purdue 68-65.
images.name: Michigan State tops Purdue late

articles.description: ESPN draft expert Jonathan Givony projects a new top 60 for the 2019 NBA draft class.
articles.headline: NBA mock draft: Five rising prospects for 2019

images.caption: De'Andre Hunter could be a first-round pick in 2019.
images.name: De'Andre Hunter [608x342]

images.caption: Niem Stevenson misses a layup, but Zhaire Smith comes out of nowhere and rises up for a two-handed dunk.
images.name: Smith elevates for epic putback slam

articles.description: Payton Pritchard had 19 points and 10 assists, and Troy Brown Jr. also had a double-double to lead Oregon past Washington State 84-57 on Sunday night.
articles.headline: Pritchard, Brown lead Oregon to 84-57 win over Washington St

articles.description: Shep Garner scored 16 points and Tony Carr had 15 points to lead Penn State to a 74-52 victory over Illinois on Sunday night.
articles.headline: Garner, Carr help Penn State beat Illinois 74-52

articles.description: After scoring a team-high 23 points, Grayson Allen credits the good ball movement to set him up in the Blue Devils' 80-69 win over the Yellow Jackets.
articles.headline: Allen credits ball movement for open looks

videos.description: Miles Bridges blocks a shot and Duke can't score after gaining possession.
videos.headline: Bridges comes up with huge block

videos.description: Kenny Goins gets the ball to Gavin Schilling, who finishes with a slam.
videos.headline: Schilling slams it down for Michigan State

videos.description: Grayson Allen makes a jumper from midrange to keep the Blue Devils in the lead.
videos.headline: Allen uses soft touch on jumper

videos.description: Marvin Bagley III gets hit in the eye by his own teammate when coming down after a rebound. Bagley is ruled out the rest of the game.
videos.headline: Bagley down after getting hit in the face

videos.description: Duke capitalizes off of a turnover with a dunk from Trevon Duval, giving them a 13-0 run on Michigan State.
videos.headline: Duval dunks to extend Blue Devils' 13-0 run

videos.description: Miles Bridges drains a three-pointer followed by a three from Jaren Jackson Jr. to cut into No. 1 Duke's lead.
videos.headline: Spartans answer Duke with back-to-back 3s

videos.description: Miles Bridges blocks another shot to stop No. 1 Duke from a basket.
videos.headline: Bridges gets another unreal block

videos.description: Trevon Duval swipes the ball and then finishes it off with a dunk for Duke.
videos.headline: Duval gets steal and slam

videos.description: Grayson Allen drains a long three-pointer and goes into halftime with 14 points.
videos.headline: Allen hits a late 3, drops 14 first-half points

videos.description: Miles Bridges hits his second three-pointer of the second half.
videos.headline: Bridges knocks down a three

videos.description: Matt McQuaid tosses a nice pass to Nick Ward who finishes the play with a layup.
videos.headline: Ward capitalizes off Duke turnover with layup

videos.description: Matt McQuiad drives for the layup gets a basket and the foul for Michigan State.
videos.headline: McQuaid gets bucket and-1

videos.description: Jaren Jackson Jr. grabs the offensive rebound and puts it back down with a two-handed flush.
videos.headline: Jackson gets second-chance dunk

videos.description: Miles Bridges drains another three to give Michigan State the lead and give Bridges 17 points.
videos.headline: Bridges hits his 5th 3-pointer

videos.description: Kenny Goins gets a great offensive rebound and then finishes the play with a slam.
videos.headline: Goins' rebound eventually leads to dunk

videos.description: Grayson Allen hits another 3-pointer giving him 32 points against Michigan State.
videos.headline: Allen stays hot with the 3-ball

videos.description: Grayson Allen continues to dominate from beyond the arc with another 3-pointer. The senior finishes with a career-high 37 points.
videos.headline: Allen hits seventh 3-pointer of game

videos.description: Grayson Allen says being on the court with Trevon Duval was key to him getting a career high of 37 points against Michigan State.
videos.headline: Allen credits teammates for career night

videos.description: With Marvin Bagley III sidelined after an eye injury, Grayson Allen takes  over draining seven 3-pointers and scoring a career-high 37 points in the Blue Devils' victory over the Spartans.
videos.headline: Allen uses career high to stop MSU
